 {"id":"cass_memory_system-zex2","title":"[Critical] LLM Cost Controls - Budget Limits and Local-Only Mode","description":"# LLM Cost Controls

## The Problem
Current plan has LLM calls in: reflect, validate, curate, context, diary extraction.
With 10 sessions/day and all features enabled, that's 50+ LLM calls/day.
At ~$0.01-0.10 per call, that's $0.50-$5.00/day = $15-150/month.

## The Solution
Make LLM usage opt-in with clear cost visibility and hard limits.

### Cost-Aware Configuration:
```typescript
interface LLMConfig {
  provider: "anthropic" | "openai" | "ollama" | "none";
  budget: {
    dailyLimit: number;  // Max $ per day, default: 0.10
    monthlyLimit: number;  // Max $ per month, default: 2.00
    warningThreshold: number;  // Warn at this %, default: 80
  };
}
```

### Local-Only Mode (Default):
```bash
# Default behavior - NO LLM CALLS
cm context "my task"  # Uses keyword search, no embeddings
cm reflect            # Extracts patterns with regex, no LLM

# Opt-in to LLM
cm reflect --llm      # Uses LLM for better extraction
cm validate --llm     # Uses LLM for validation
```

### Cost Transparency:
```bash
$ cm reflect --llm

Reflecting on 3 sessions...
Extracted 5 potential rules.
Cost: $0.03 (Daily: $0.08/$0.10, Monthly: $0.45/$2.00)

$ cm usage
Today:     $0.08 / $0.10 (80%) ⚠️
This month: $0.45 / $2.00 (22%)
All time:  $1.23
```

## Why This Is Critical
- Users are cost-sensitive
- Surprise bills = angry users = uninstalls
- Local-first is privacy-friendly AND cost-friendly
- LLM should enhance, not be required","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-07T17:08:16.006476-05:00","updated_at":"2025-12-07T17:53:57.710792-05:00","comments":[{"id":40,"issue_id":"cass_memory_system-zex2","author":"jemanuel","text":"## Problem: LLM Cost Explosion
